# AI Coding Agent Memory & Rules File

This file outlines the goals of the project, the premium beige scrapbook design outlines, the technology stack, and the precise "current issue" context. All AI agents working on this repository must read this file first and adhere to these guidelines.

---

## 🚀 1. PROJECT GOALS & FUNCTIONALITY
The project is a **React + TypeScript landing page and sharing platform** backed by **PocketBase** as the backend.

### Key Features:
- **Scrapbook Landing Page**: A premium, interactive landing page showcasing shared memories, featuring a custom 3D flipping-page scrapbook book component.
- **Google OAuth2 Signup/Login**: Auths users via Google with requested `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/youtube.upload` scopes so that the platform can upload videos to YouTube on behalf of the user.
- **User Profiles**: Logged-in users can view their uploaded YouTube videos, manage their profile, and create "boards".
- **Memory Boards**: Public/shared spaces where users can pin their polaroid-style videos into a cohesive scrapbook layout.

---

## 🎨 2. THE DESIGN SYSTEM: BEIGE SCRAPBOOK AESTHETIC
Aesthetics are critical. The design must feel warm, analog, premium, tactile, and highly responsive.
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Tailwind CSS v4** is now the styling layer (installed via `@tailwindcss/vite`). Custom design tokens live in `@theme` inside `src/index.css`.
> **Exceptions**: GSAP 3D book structural styles → `src/styles/book3d.css`. CSS keyframe animations (marquee, spin) → `src/styles/animations.css`.
> **No Generic Colors or Placeholders.** Use curated HSL palettes and dynamic assets generated via image tools.

### Visual Elements:
- **Paper Textures & Notebook Lines**: Uses radial gradients and repeating linear-gradients to emulate premium notebook pages, high-quality linen textures, and textured covers.
- **Tape & Stamps**: Semi-transparent, rotated tapes on pictures, organic shadow stamps (`box-shadow`), and tactile hover effects.
- **Polaroid Frames**: Video cards must be rendered inside highly styled polaroid frames (`.polaroid`) with organic tilts, custom cursors, and drop-shadows.
- **Interactive 3D Books**: The custom `BookComponent.tsx` uses GSAP to animate a 3D book cover that swings open (`rotateY: -150`) and loops flipping pages infinitely when hovered, presenting text and memories inside.
- **Harmonious Palette**:
  - Warm beige paper: `#fbf8f0` / `#faf6eb` / `#f7f2e4`
  - Rich leather covers: `#4a2f1b` / spine `#2b170c`
  - Accent / Gold foil: `#d4af37`
  - Vibrant coral accent: `#be4a2a`

---

## 🛠️ 3. TECH STACK & SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE
- **Frontend**: React 19, TypeScript, Vite, React Router DOM v7, GSAP.
- **Backend**: PocketBase v0.27.0 (served locally).
- **Environment**: Managed using Bun (running package scripts).
- **Ports & Dev Configuration**:
  - Frontend: `http://localhost:3000` (Vite dev server)
  - PocketBase: `http://localhost:8090` (Serving via `pb/pocketbase serve --dir=pb/pb_data`)
  - Admin Dashboard: `http://localhost:8090/_/`

---

## ⚠️ 4. THE ACTIVE ISSUE: DATA STRUCTURE — PAGES RETRIEVAL

### Problem
PocketBase does **not** back-point `Books` to `Pages`. `BookRecord` has no `pages` field. The relation is **forward-only**: each `PageRecord` has an optional `book` field (the parent book ID). Accessing `book.pages` in any component is always wrong — it will be `undefined`.

### Canonical Pattern: Lift & Filter in `Profile.tsx`
`Profile.tsx` is the **single data-fetching owner**. It already loads all pages via `loadPages()`. The correct approach is:

1. Derive `selectedBookPages` in `Profile.tsx` by filtering the in-memory `pages` array.
2. Pass the filtered, sorted array **down as a prop** to `SelectedBook` — never fetch inside `SelectedBook`.

```ts
// In Profile.tsx
const selectedBookPages = pages
  .filter((p) => p.book === selectedBookId)
  .sort((a, b) => (a.order ?? 0) - (b.order ?? 0));
```

```tsx
// Call site
<SelectedBook
  book={selectedBook}
  pages={selectedBookPages}
  currentPageIndex={currentPageIndex}
  onPageChange={setCurrentPageIndex}
/>
```

### SelectedBook Props Contract
```tsx
interface SelectedBookProps {
  book: BookRecord | null;
  pages: PageRecord[];          // pre-filtered & sorted by Profile.tsx
  currentPageIndex: number;
  onPageChange: (index: number) => void;
}
```

### When to Use a Per-Book Fetch Instead
Only reach for a filtered fetch if page counts across all books grow very large (hundreds+). In that case:
```ts
pb.collection('pages').getFullList({ filter: `book="${bookId}"`, sort: 'order' })
```
Trigger this inside a `useEffect` watching `selectedBookId` change.
